{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:galatians.6",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 6 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:1",
      "text": "Brethren, if a man be overtaken in a fault, ye which are spiritual, restore such an one in the spirit of meekness; considering thyself, lest thou also be tempted.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:2",
      "text": "Bear ye one another’s burdens, and so fulfil the law of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:3",
      "text": "For if a man think himself to be something, when he is nothing, he deceiveth himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:4",
      "text": "But let every man prove his own work, and then shall he have rejoicing in himself alone, and not in another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:5",
      "text": "For every man shall bear his own burden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:6",
      "text": "Let him that is taught in the word communicate unto him that teacheth in all good things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:7",
      "text": "Be not deceived; God is not mocked: for whatsoever a man soweth, that shall he also reap.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:8",
      "text": "For he that soweth to his flesh shall of the flesh reap corruption; but he that soweth to the Spirit shall of the Spirit reap life everlasting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:9",
      "text": "And let us not be weary in well doing: for in due season we shall reap, if we faint not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:10",
      "text": "As we have therefore opportunity, let us do good unto all men, especially unto them who are of the household of faith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:11",
      "text": "Ye see how large a letter I have written unto you with mine own hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:12",
      "text": "As many as desire to make a fair shew in the flesh, they constrain you to be circumcised; only lest they should suffer persecution for the cross of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:13",
      "text": "For neither they themselves who are circumcised keep the law; but desire to have you circumcised, that they may glory in your flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:14",
      "text": "But God forbid that I should glory, save in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom the world is crucified unto me, and I unto the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:15",
      "text": "For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision availeth any thing, nor uncircumcision, but a new creature.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:16",
      "text": "And as many as walk according to this rule, peace be on them, and mercy, and upon the Israel of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:17",
      "text": "From henceforth let no man trouble me: for I bear in my body the marks of the Lord Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:galatians.6.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:18",
      "text": "Brethren, the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
